The discovery of two snow leopard brothers in Zhenda Town of southwest China's Sichuan Province sent forest rangers into high spirits until they laterÂ learned that one of them was injured during a fight over territory. Watch this episode to find out more about the big cat living in China's plateaus. About 'Journeys in Nature': Sanjiangyuan series In the Sanjiangyuan Series, we present the stunning landscapes and abundant wildlife of the Sanjiangyuan Region, where the Yangtze, Yellow and Lancang rivers all originate. Sanjiangyuan has earned the title "Water tower of China," because the abundant glacier resources here have a freshwater reserve of 200 billion cubic meters. The precious water has nurtured numerous wild flora and fauna like snow leopards, Himalayan blue sheep, Thorold's deer, Tibetan wild asses, and vultures. List of episodes Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep.1: Sources of Life Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 2: Jinsha River Overture Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 3: Alpine Wetlands Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 4: Dancers on the Cliff Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 5: Thorold's Deer Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 6: Elves in the Snow Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 7: Plateau Wanderers Journeys in Nature: Sanjiangyuan series | Ep. 8: King of the Sky (Cover image a video screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)